column7: "The name Amoy is an English transliteration of the Zhangzhou pronunciation of the words 厦门 (pronounced Xiamen in Standard Mandarin and E-mng in Standard Hokkien.) The Zhangzhou Hokkien pronunciation was used instead of Standard Xiamen Hokkien because of the overwhelming numbers of Zhangzhou people who left Amoy (now Xiamen) in China to settle in Singapore through the city's port." - Wikipedia

"...among the explanations for the name ‘Siglap’ is a local legend that attributed it to a Malay chieftain, Tok Lasam, who upon first landing in the area during a particularly dark thunderstorm, called it ‘Si-gelap’, which translated literally from Malay means ‘darkness that conceals’." - http://www.mysiglap.org/who-we-are/history
